# Copy to ".env" and fill in. Restart `npm run dev` after changes.
#
# --- Production build (`npm run build`) ---
# • Defaults: API at same origin `/api`, uploads at `/uploads` (configure nginx/Caddy to proxy to Spring Boot).
# • Split hosts: set at build time, e.g. VITE_API_URL=https://api.yoursite.com/api
# • SEO canonicals: VITE_SITE_URL=https://www.yoursite.com
# • Docker image (backend repo `deploy/docker-compose.prod.yml`): same values via compose build args.
# Create an OAuth 2.0 Client ID (Web application) in Google Cloud Console:
# APIs & Services → Credentials → Create Credentials → OAuth client ID
# Authorized JavaScript origins: http://localhost:5173
# Authorized redirect URIs: not required for the token popup flow used here.
#
# You can set the same value as GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID on the backend instead; the app
# will fetch it from GET /api/auth/google-client-id when this line is omitted.

VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=

# Optional: full API base URL. Dev default is "/api" (Vite proxy).
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8082/api

# Dev proxy target — must match Docker’s published host port (`docker ps`, e.g. :8082->8081).
# Compose default BACKEND_PORT is 8082; if you use BACKEND_PORT=8081, set this to http://127.0.0.1:8081
# VITE_DEV_API_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:8082
